1
00:00:04,338 --> 00:00:06,741
<i>"I try to communicate something</i>

2
00:00:06,807 --> 00:00:07,641
MAY, 2015

3
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:09,510
<i>and self-destruct."</i>

4
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,281
Yes?

5
00:00:14,782 --> 00:00:16,150
Your future goals.

6
00:00:17,251 --> 00:00:18,085
Submit them soon.

7
00:00:18,819 --> 00:00:21,122
<i>"That day,</i>

8
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:23,924
<i>I confessed my love to you.</i>

9
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:27,294
<i>Something came over me."</i>

10
00:00:28,729 --> 00:00:29,830
Ms. Suenaga!

11
00:00:35,269 --> 00:00:36,303
Ms. Suenaga.

12
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:39,974
I…

13
00:00:41,275 --> 00:00:43,210
I've fallen in love with you.

14
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,015
I've fallen for you!

15
00:00:51,185 --> 00:00:52,019
I don't

16
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:54,522
have a single clue

17
00:00:57,158 --> 00:00:58,592
about what to do.

18
00:01:10,838 --> 00:01:15,443
I thought you hated me.

19
00:01:20,314 --> 00:01:21,148
Thank you.

20
00:01:35,763 --> 00:01:37,832
<i>A student told you he loved you?</i>

21
00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:40,668
It's that Kuroiwa boy I mentioned before.

22
00:01:41,769 --> 00:01:43,237
The problematic one?

23
00:01:44,105 --> 00:01:48,275
So he was acting out because he had
feelings for you or something?

24
00:01:51,645 --> 00:01:52,746
Go.

25
00:01:52,813 --> 00:01:55,616
He wasn't that serious.

26
00:01:55,683 --> 00:01:59,753
He was like
"I've fallen in love with you."

27
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:00,654
I think.

28
00:02:00,721 --> 00:02:03,224
"I've fallen in love with you."

29
00:02:03,858 --> 00:02:07,027
What is that,
a punishment for losing a bet?

30
00:02:07,094 --> 00:02:08,496
Maybe.

31
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:10,464
Most likely.

32
00:02:11,232 --> 00:02:13,033
It's like we're not here.

33
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,639
You got a crush, don't you?

34
00:02:18,706 --> 00:02:20,040
It's all over your face.

35
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,910
I'm so right.

36
00:02:23,677 --> 00:02:24,778
Did you tell her?

37
00:02:25,513 --> 00:02:28,315
Go out on a date yet?

38
00:02:28,382 --> 00:02:29,483
It's not like that.

39
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:33,521
I heard you and your mom
got in a fight again.

40
00:02:36,657 --> 00:02:40,027
I'm a pacifist who hates conflict.

41
00:02:41,629 --> 00:02:44,398
I'm happy to mediate whenever you need.

42
00:02:47,301 --> 00:02:51,338
If she doesn't want to tell me,
then I don't care anymore.

43
00:02:54,775 --> 00:02:58,479
-You forgot to say grace.
-Thank you for the food.

44
00:02:59,813 --> 00:03:02,616
-Don't touch--
-It's from Dad.

45
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:04,418
Stop! Give that here!

46
00:03:04,485 --> 00:03:07,054
You don't need to read it!

47
00:03:07,121 --> 00:03:07,988
AS HIS FATHER…

48
00:03:08,055 --> 00:03:09,657
I WANT TO MEET AKIRA

49
00:03:14,261 --> 00:03:18,399
-And you told Shotaro you can't go?
-Yes, for now.

50
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:23,971
Will you marry me?

51
00:03:24,038 --> 00:03:27,708
I want to keep teaching here until
my students graduate,

52
00:03:29,076 --> 00:03:31,078
and get married next year.

53
00:03:31,145 --> 00:03:33,113
Then why do you keep eyeing your phone?

54
00:03:34,682 --> 00:03:36,817
I haven't heard from him since.

55
00:03:37,351 --> 00:03:38,285
What?

56
00:03:38,986 --> 00:03:42,056
Shotaro's bummed!

57
00:03:42,122 --> 00:03:45,559
I get it, it's a lot easier
when you decide to get married

58
00:03:45,626 --> 00:03:49,797
get swept up and hitched,
and reach the finish line.

59
00:03:49,863 --> 00:03:53,601
If you miss your timing,
it really dampens things.

60
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:55,236
-Marriage is momentum.
-Really?

61
00:03:55,302 --> 00:03:56,870
Yeah. It was with us.

62
00:03:56,937 --> 00:03:59,974
I moved in with my husband
three months after meeting him,

63
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,742
and then got married at Mach speed.

64
00:04:01,809 --> 00:04:05,746
Yeah, momentum is really important.
It's the same for all weddings.

65
00:04:07,114 --> 00:04:09,850
-I'm not sure it's like that for everyone.
-It is.

66
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:12,586
-Is it really?
-I'm telling you it is!

67
00:04:12,653 --> 00:04:14,655
-Mach speed.
-Mach speed?

68
00:04:16,557 --> 00:04:19,193
<i>What are you doing next weekend?</i>

69
00:04:20,027 --> 00:04:21,929
<i>Maybe I'll come to Osaka.</i>

70
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:25,032
KOBOSHIDAIRA

71
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:26,467
OSAKA

72
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:29,903
She was so happy when I proposed.

73
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:32,306
Now she wants to keep teaching.

74
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:37,177
Like where did all that excitement go?

75
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:39,913
You thought she'd quit right away.

76
00:04:40,581 --> 00:04:46,954
I, the great and handsome Shotaro Kawai
who has everything to offer

77
00:04:47,021 --> 00:04:51,091
asked you to be my wife,
so get over to Osaka and take care of me.

78
00:04:52,059 --> 00:04:54,295
You make me sound like a real bastard.

79
00:04:55,963 --> 00:04:59,433
You thought she'd just rush over,
but she pressed pause instead.

80
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,202
I'm sure it hurt your pride.

81
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:05,272
It's making me a little sad
you putting it that way.

82
00:05:07,675 --> 00:05:12,212
I hate that there might be a sleazy
part of me that actually feels that way.

83
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,781
Yes.

84
00:05:14,848 --> 00:05:16,884
Speaking of sleazy. That night…

85
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:20,754
-Is this an invitation?
-I'm just hungry.

86
00:05:22,456 --> 00:05:23,457
So?

87
00:05:23,957 --> 00:05:24,958
You coming?

88
00:05:29,697 --> 00:05:32,199
I graciously decline your offer.

89
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:37,037
I was just offering you dinner
out of the kindness of my heart.

90
00:05:37,104 --> 00:05:37,805
I'm sorry.

91
00:05:37,871 --> 00:05:40,541
You acted like I was trying
to sleep with you.

92
00:05:40,607 --> 00:05:43,143
I didn't think we should be alone.

93
00:05:43,711 --> 00:05:47,081
But I was overthinking it
since you have a girlfriend.

94
00:05:54,121 --> 00:05:55,055
Whoa.

95
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:57,257
Wait, um…

96
00:05:58,792 --> 00:06:00,627
What's happening now?

97
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:02,329
Be careful.

98
00:06:02,396 --> 00:06:04,765
-Up we go.
-Sorry.

99
00:06:05,799 --> 00:06:07,968
I'm a little drunk.

100
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:11,004
You didn't need to drink that much. Okay.

101
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:14,108
We're here.

102
00:06:14,174 --> 00:06:16,076
Okay, put on your shoes.

103
00:06:17,344 --> 00:06:19,079
This isn't funny.

104
00:06:19,613 --> 00:06:21,849
Come on, put them on.

105
00:06:21,915 --> 00:06:23,083
Okay.

106
00:06:25,486 --> 00:06:26,653
Watch out!

107
00:06:28,655 --> 00:06:31,792
You're so thin.
How do you even fit your organs?

108
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:43,103
What's wrong?

109
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:44,938
I got off early, so I came to see you.

110
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:52,112
-Did he force you to drink?
-I didn't do anything.

111
00:06:56,116 --> 00:06:57,651
See you.

112
00:07:08,162 --> 00:07:10,664
They switched to their summer
uniforms today.

113
00:07:10,731 --> 00:07:11,498
Good morning.

114
00:07:11,565 --> 00:07:14,234
-They look so cool.
-Good morning.

115
00:07:14,868 --> 00:07:16,303
Good morning.

116
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:21,608
Good morning, Kuroiwa.

117
00:07:21,675 --> 00:07:24,278
You're supposed to switch
to your summer uniform today.

118
00:07:25,846 --> 00:07:27,948
I didn't notice until I turned the corner.

119
00:07:28,649 --> 00:07:30,250
It's too late now.

120
00:07:37,157 --> 00:07:38,058
Good morning.

121
00:07:38,826 --> 00:07:40,260
Kuroiwa!

122
00:07:41,228 --> 00:07:43,030
Sorry, thought you were a target.

123
00:07:43,096 --> 00:07:45,866
-What's up?
-Still the winter uniform?

124
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:48,435
-You did it on purpose.
-No.

125
00:07:48,502 --> 00:07:51,472
-Good morning.
-You have makeup on!

126
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:53,540
Good morning.

127
00:07:55,209 --> 00:07:56,643
'Morning.

128
00:07:56,710 --> 00:07:58,078
-Hello.
-Hello.

129
00:08:15,295 --> 00:08:18,031
Wait, we're covering that in class now.

130
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:27,407
Any sections you need help with?

131
00:08:30,711 --> 00:08:31,712
Well…

132
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,584
Let's see.

133
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,465
Why didn't you sit next to me?

134
00:08:58,071 --> 00:09:01,108
I've been thinking since then.

135
00:09:01,675 --> 00:09:02,943
About what?

136
00:09:08,549 --> 00:09:12,152
I don't think loving you is enough.

137
00:09:17,291 --> 00:09:18,125
I…

138
00:09:20,961 --> 00:09:24,164
I want you to fall in love with me

139
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:27,968
too.

140
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:36,743
Sorry.

141
00:09:40,581 --> 00:09:43,817
That's something I can't do.

142
00:09:52,826 --> 00:09:54,895
EBIHARA, VERY GOOD JOB.

143
00:10:04,571 --> 00:10:07,307
<i>Sorry, I'm visiting my folks this weekend.</i>

144
00:10:07,374 --> 00:10:09,409
<i>I haven't told them we're engaged yet.</i>

145
00:10:11,745 --> 00:10:13,614
<i>I'd like to pay my respects too.</i>

146
00:10:15,549 --> 00:10:17,951
I'D LIKE TO PAY MY RESPECTS TOO.

147
00:10:18,018 --> 00:10:19,086
<i>Okay!</i>

148
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,463
-You can do it!
-Keep going!

149
00:10:29,529 --> 00:10:30,998
Go, Kuroiwa!

150
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:34,835
Go, Akira!

151
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:36,103
Kuroiwa's so fast.

152
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:38,472
-Go!
-Akira!

153
00:10:42,309 --> 00:10:45,178
<i>I wanted to see Shotaro.</i>

154
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:48,315
<i>But why?</i>

155
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:57,891
KUROIWA

156
00:11:12,673 --> 00:11:15,342
<i>I'm going to keep my distance for now.</i>

157
00:11:37,617 --> 00:11:39,385
Sport's Day is coming up.

158
00:11:40,353 --> 00:11:43,723
There have been
a number of changes this year.

159
00:11:44,290 --> 00:11:46,292
First, no group gymnastics.

160
00:11:46,926 --> 00:11:50,496
For the obstacle course,
we'll place mats under the balance beam

161
00:11:50,563 --> 00:11:54,934
and have students remove hair accessories
before they crawl under the net.

162
00:11:55,001 --> 00:11:58,471
-And absolutely no pets allowed.
-Pets?

163
00:11:58,538 --> 00:12:01,541
And make sure they don't pitch
any tents in the schoolyard.

164
00:12:01,607 --> 00:12:02,875
Tents?

165
00:12:03,543 --> 00:12:04,644
We need to be careful.

166
00:12:05,478 --> 00:12:09,315
This is way more concerning,
spreading all these false rumors.

167
00:12:09,382 --> 00:12:11,417
We can't delete them fast enough.

168
00:12:11,484 --> 00:12:13,586
Stay on top of the information management.

169
00:12:13,653 --> 00:12:14,287
Yes, ma'am.

170
00:12:14,353 --> 00:12:17,223
HER FIANCE IS THE HEAD OF AN IT COMPANY
HE OWNS AN ISLAND IN THE CARRIBEAN

171
00:12:19,092 --> 00:12:23,329
IT'S SO OBVIOUS THAT THIRD YEAR
XXXXIWA'S GOT A THING FOR HIJIRI.

172
00:12:28,801 --> 00:12:30,737
THREE-EIGHT

173
00:12:31,804 --> 00:12:33,906
Cut it out already.

174
00:12:33,973 --> 00:12:36,209
So that boy was serious.

175
00:12:36,275 --> 00:12:38,778
"I want you to fall in love with me."

176
00:12:38,845 --> 00:12:39,712
Very serious.

177
00:12:39,779 --> 00:12:41,848
I don't know how seriously to take it.

178
00:12:43,382 --> 00:12:44,617
But I'll be careful.

179
00:12:44,684 --> 00:12:46,185
I'll keep my distance.

180
00:12:46,252 --> 00:12:47,587
Try not to agitate him.

181
00:12:48,488 --> 00:12:49,689
Good idea.

182
00:12:51,524 --> 00:12:54,427
Just remembered, I bought these
as they were on sale. Here!

183
00:12:55,128 --> 00:12:56,996
Thank you, I will gladly accept it.

184
00:13:00,066 --> 00:13:01,434
What? You're going out?

185
00:13:01,501 --> 00:13:04,337
-I'm going to visit Shotaro's parents.
-His parents?

186
00:13:04,403 --> 00:13:06,405
<i>Just dropping by to pay my respects.</i>

187
00:13:06,472 --> 00:13:08,574
You're girlfriend is visiting
your parents?

188
00:13:09,909 --> 00:13:10,743
How'd you know?

189
00:13:10,810 --> 00:13:12,111
Konishi told me.

190
00:13:12,779 --> 00:13:13,613
That's scary.

191
00:13:13,679 --> 00:13:16,182
Huh? Word really gets around fast.

192
00:13:17,116 --> 00:13:20,520
-I'll keep to myself then.
-I know your plan.

193
00:13:20,586 --> 00:13:24,490
You're going to use your parents
to pressure her to come to Osaka,

194
00:13:24,557 --> 00:13:27,326
so she'll be in reach, you sly tactician.

195
00:13:27,393 --> 00:13:30,763
I can only imagine what you think of me.

196
00:13:31,898 --> 00:13:34,433
Just a little neighborly warning.

197
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,803
-Yes?
-Families can be tricky.

198
00:13:36,869 --> 00:13:41,040
My married friends
all have issues with their in-laws.

199
00:13:41,808 --> 00:13:44,210
The sooner the families meet, the better.

200
00:13:45,011 --> 00:13:47,814
I'll take my consultation fee now.

201
00:13:48,714 --> 00:13:51,851
I believe I took care of you
when you got blackout drunk.

202
00:13:51,918 --> 00:13:54,320
Not to mention
I got knocked down for my trouble.

203
00:13:55,488 --> 00:13:56,923
She gets jealous easily.

204
00:13:58,391 --> 00:14:00,693
-I have tomorrow's presentation materials.
-Thanks.

205
00:14:10,036 --> 00:14:12,839
<i>I know it's sudden but</i>
<i>would you like to invite your parents?</i>

206
00:14:12,905 --> 00:14:13,940
What?

207
00:14:15,775 --> 00:14:16,809
Your parents?

208
00:14:16,876 --> 00:14:19,545
<i>I asked my folks,</i>
<i>and they invited them to dinner.</i>

209
00:14:19,612 --> 00:14:23,282
-Wait, my parents are going too?
-Their first meeting?

210
00:14:23,349 --> 00:14:25,484
-<i>Is it too short notice?</i>
<i>-</i>Yes!

211
00:14:25,551 --> 00:14:27,820
What will you do? You need to change!

212
00:14:27,887 --> 00:14:29,088
First, I'll call my…

213
00:14:31,190 --> 00:14:34,093
-Hey Mom, can you make it?
-Your hair.

214
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,562
-Let's put your hair up.
-Ow!

215
00:14:36,629 --> 00:14:38,297
Have a nice day.

216
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:42,668
They're out? Why now?

217
00:14:44,370 --> 00:14:45,705
What's wrong?

218
00:14:45,771 --> 00:14:49,075
The manufacturers are backing
out of the India deal.

219
00:14:49,141 --> 00:14:51,410
-What?
-Were the price terms too harsh?

220
00:14:51,477 --> 00:14:53,112
Or they got poached?

221
00:14:53,179 --> 00:14:55,248
It's okay, I will convince them.

222
00:14:55,314 --> 00:14:57,550
-Konishi, call the chief!
-Yes, ma'am!

223
00:14:57,617 --> 00:14:59,986
Send this to Vietnam and India.

224
00:15:01,354 --> 00:15:03,789
We're counting on you.

225
00:15:04,357 --> 00:15:05,791
You can't make it?

226
00:15:05,858 --> 00:15:08,494
Sorry, there's a work emergency.

227
00:15:09,629 --> 00:15:12,131
I can't get out of it.
Sorry could you go without me.

228
00:15:12,198 --> 00:15:15,401
What? Just me and our parents?

229
00:15:15,468 --> 00:15:17,436
I'm really sorry! I'll call you later!

230
00:15:17,503 --> 00:15:18,337
Wai--

231
00:15:24,710 --> 00:15:25,544
What?

232
00:15:26,979 --> 00:15:30,149
-Kawai, good work on your day off.
-What?

233
00:15:30,216 --> 00:15:32,184
You may go. Make sure to make it up.

234
00:15:32,251 --> 00:15:33,920
But we're in a crisis!

235
00:15:34,587 --> 00:15:38,124
This is Konishi's account, and
the presentation is tomorrow.

236
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:41,127
To be blunt, you being here
would change nothing.

237
00:15:41,193 --> 00:15:44,497
-Maybe, but there's a chance I--
-Are you thick?

238
00:15:44,563 --> 00:15:47,066
I'm saying go meet each other's families.

239
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:50,036
Pulling out last minute
will impact their faith in you.

240
00:15:50,102 --> 00:15:52,538
And again, you being here will
change nothing.

241
00:15:52,605 --> 00:15:54,407
That's a bit hurtful.

242
00:15:56,242 --> 00:15:58,811
But if someone asks you where you went,

243
00:15:58,878 --> 00:16:01,580
I'll probably have to act angry.

244
00:16:01,647 --> 00:16:03,649
-Just a heads up.
-I won't go then!

245
00:16:03,716 --> 00:16:05,184
I'll be angry now if you don't!

246
00:16:11,457 --> 00:16:12,525
Thank you!

247
00:16:14,193 --> 00:16:15,328
Hijiri!

248
00:16:15,394 --> 00:16:16,595
You made it!

249
00:16:16,662 --> 00:16:19,899
-I'm sorry this was so sudden.
-Do you think this outfit is okay?

250
00:16:19,966 --> 00:16:22,601
When I pulled it out, it was so wrinkled.

251
00:16:22,668 --> 00:16:24,503
I frantically ironed it.

252
00:16:24,570 --> 00:16:26,706
You're taking this too seriously.

253
00:16:26,772 --> 00:16:28,975
We're not going to some mansion.

254
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:30,276
-Right?
-Yeah.

255
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,178
Oh, my…

256
00:16:32,845 --> 00:16:37,450
-What an impressive house.
-It really is.

257
00:16:37,516 --> 00:16:42,154
-I'm so sorry for the sudden invitation.
-Alright!

258
00:16:42,221 --> 00:16:46,225
-And Shotaro can't even make it.
-I'm sorry about this.

259
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:50,096
-We hate to intrude.
-Thank you for your hospitality.

260
