So…

514
00:33:18,648 --> 00:33:20,249
Trade with mine.

515
00:33:20,316 --> 00:33:24,253
I've been worried about Akira's
recent erratic behavior,

516
00:33:24,887 --> 00:33:26,389
then I see they're so close.

517
00:33:27,957 --> 00:33:31,060
First loves can be so cute.

518
00:33:31,661 --> 00:33:35,498
Exchanging headbands with
your crush seems to be popular.

519
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:41,871
But seeing him suddenly get a crush,

520
00:33:41,938 --> 00:33:45,975
I realize he'll soon start dating
and then get married,

521
00:33:46,042 --> 00:33:48,344
and before too long
will be leaving the nest.

522
00:33:49,012 --> 00:33:51,347
Yes, one day.

523
00:33:53,583 --> 00:33:55,451
What kind of adult will he become?

524
00:33:57,420 --> 00:34:01,290
As long as he can keep laughing
and he's happy,

525
00:34:02,458 --> 00:34:04,360
that's all that matters.

526
00:34:06,763 --> 00:34:10,233
I hope I can help as his teacher.

527
00:34:11,067 --> 00:34:12,168
Sincerely.

528
00:34:14,971 --> 00:34:17,440
That's reassuring, Ms. Suenaga.

529
00:34:19,642 --> 00:34:20,743
Thank you.

530
00:34:25,748 --> 00:34:27,617
Yuko Kawashima.

531
00:34:28,618 --> 00:34:30,286
Kosuke Tsubota.

532
00:34:31,754 --> 00:34:34,390
Here you go.

533
00:34:36,659 --> 00:34:38,327
-Ms. Suenaga.
-Here.

534
00:34:40,363 --> 00:34:45,401
<i>Okay, all second years gather up</i>
<i>for the ball rolling event!</i>

535
00:34:47,970 --> 00:34:48,905
<i>Gather round!</i>

536
00:34:48,971 --> 00:34:52,975
<i>The next event will be</i>
<i>the second year girls'…</i>

537
00:35:26,006 --> 00:35:29,643
<i>Yamamoto from Class 3-2…</i>

538
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:33,914
What is this?
You need to stop messing around.

539
00:35:37,585 --> 00:35:38,419
Why?

540
00:35:40,621 --> 00:35:43,924
Why are you actively avoiding
looking at or talking to me?

541
00:35:47,061 --> 00:35:48,796
Is it because I said I liked you?

542
00:35:52,133 --> 00:35:53,667
Of course not.

543
00:35:53,734 --> 00:35:56,804
It may not look it, but I'm pretty busy.
You're overly concerned.

544
00:35:56,871 --> 00:35:59,640
Now come on, the relay is next.

545
00:36:01,809 --> 00:36:08,115
<i>Once again, group A for the relay</i>
<i>semi-finals, please come to the gate.</i>

546
00:36:08,182 --> 00:36:09,917
Don't treat me like a kid.

547
00:36:14,021 --> 00:36:15,589
Why are you running away?

548
00:36:20,227 --> 00:36:21,729
Let me be clear then.

549
00:36:23,464 --> 00:36:24,965
I don't appreciate this.

550
00:36:25,933 --> 00:36:26,800
So stop.

551
00:36:31,705 --> 00:36:34,108
I will root for you as your teacher.

552
00:36:35,543 --> 00:36:37,244
Nothing more, nothing less.

553
00:36:40,614 --> 00:36:41,715
So please stop.

554
00:36:56,330 --> 00:36:57,398
<i>What is this?</i>

555
00:36:58,933 --> 00:36:59,967
<i>It's not right.</i>

556
00:37:03,304 --> 00:37:06,807
<i>I thought it was supposed</i>
<i>to be something special.</i>

557
00:37:09,076 --> 00:37:09,910
<i>Love.</i>

558
00:37:12,379 --> 00:37:13,914
<i>And they're off!</i>

559
00:37:13,981 --> 00:37:16,050
<i>Red team is in the lead…</i>

560
00:37:22,623 --> 00:37:24,658
Ms. Haraguchi is being taken off?

561
00:37:24,725 --> 00:37:27,061
The India project leader is a hard ass.

562
00:37:27,127 --> 00:37:27,962
But why?

563
00:37:28,696 --> 00:37:30,231
That mistake of ours…

564
00:37:30,864 --> 00:37:33,801
It was a setup from the beginning.

565
00:37:33,867 --> 00:37:36,937
You know the rumors with her and the boss.

566
00:37:37,004 --> 00:37:38,672
It's office politics.

567
00:37:38,739 --> 00:37:40,574
No…

568
00:37:44,445 --> 00:37:47,248
-Hey!
-We received a phone call.

569
00:37:47,314 --> 00:37:50,551
They'd like another meeting when
they're back next month.

570
00:37:51,719 --> 00:37:53,921
-What?
-We need Ms. Haraguchi.

571
00:37:55,222 --> 00:37:57,558
I'm sorry.
I know it's not my place to say this.

572
00:37:58,192 --> 00:37:59,793
-But she's needed.
-Kawai.

573
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:03,964
She's close with the locals, and being
the boss's mistress is just a rumor.

574
00:38:04,031 --> 00:38:06,567
-She has someone--
-Our presentation was a success.

575
00:38:08,168 --> 00:38:10,571
-What?
-They accepted the deal.

576
00:38:10,638 --> 00:38:12,039
I was just telling the chief.

577
00:38:13,574 --> 00:38:15,876
Is that right?

578
00:38:16,510 --> 00:38:19,913
What's this about the boss's what?

579
00:38:19,980 --> 00:38:22,483
Well, that's…

580
00:38:22,549 --> 00:38:25,185
Is an explanation required?

581
00:38:25,252 --> 00:38:29,256
Well, I heard what I heard.

582
00:38:30,157 --> 00:38:32,526
-My wing's broken.
-What?

583
00:38:32,593 --> 00:38:34,395
I can't believe I had to tell him

584
00:38:34,461 --> 00:38:38,065
that there was a rumor
about me and the boss.

585
00:38:38,132 --> 00:38:41,201
-My wing's broken.
-You mean spirit?

586
00:38:42,169 --> 00:38:43,504
-Kawai.
-Yes?

587
00:38:43,570 --> 00:38:46,573
-You get caught by the dumbest things.
-I'm sorry.

588
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:49,576
Do you get that my
spirit and wing is broken

589
00:38:49,643 --> 00:38:51,545
because you decided to butt in?

590
00:38:51,612 --> 00:38:53,180
I'm sorry!

591
00:38:53,747 --> 00:39:00,421
I couldn't help myself after I heard from
Konishi that you were being taken off.

592
00:39:00,487 --> 00:39:02,790
I'm going to have to throttle Konishi.

593
00:39:03,624 --> 00:39:07,027
But it's better now that
the rumor was put to rest.

594
00:39:07,995 --> 00:39:11,532
-What?
-Might as well go out with me.

595
00:39:12,266 --> 00:39:13,133
What?

596
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:15,436
<i>We're down to the final event.</i>

597
00:39:15,502 --> 00:39:20,240
<i>It will be the school-wide team relay!</i>

598
00:39:21,375 --> 00:39:25,179
We're counting on you, Anchor!

599
00:39:28,315 --> 00:39:29,717
Huh? Kuroiwa?

600
00:39:30,484 --> 00:39:32,419
You got this!

601
00:39:34,388 --> 00:39:36,490
Huh? Kuroiwa?

602
00:39:36,557 --> 00:39:39,059
Ms. Suenaga! Kuroiwa's missing!

603
00:40:00,612 --> 00:40:01,446
My keys.

604
00:40:07,219 --> 00:40:10,389
Don't hang up, you idiot.

605
00:40:13,959 --> 00:40:15,694
I managed to reach him.

606
00:40:16,395 --> 00:40:18,764
He went home because he
wasn't feeling well.

607
00:40:19,698 --> 00:40:23,268
But then he felt better
and decided to go out.

608
00:40:23,335 --> 00:40:24,503
Did he mention where?

609
00:40:24,569 --> 00:40:26,104
That's when he hung up.

610
00:40:26,671 --> 00:40:29,741
I'm so sorry for causing such a commotion!

611
00:40:30,308 --> 00:40:33,578
Please contact us if anything happens.

612
00:40:33,645 --> 00:40:37,749
Yes, I'll be sure to give him
a proper scolding later.

613
00:40:38,750 --> 00:40:41,052
-I'm so sorry.
-Take care now.

614
00:40:41,119 --> 00:40:43,889
-I'm so sorry.
-Please take care now.

615
00:40:43,955 --> 00:40:44,923
I'm so sorry.

616
00:40:48,193 --> 00:40:50,896
I think that wraps things up on our end.

617
00:40:50,962 --> 00:40:55,333
I can't believe he went home
right before the relay.

618
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:57,102
He needs to face consequences!

619
00:40:57,169 --> 00:41:02,274
Kuroiwa has caused a little
too much trouble lately.

620
00:41:04,576 --> 00:41:06,745
Any reason he might be acting out?

621
00:41:07,579 --> 00:41:09,648
Now come on, the relay is next.

622
00:41:10,215 --> 00:41:11,316
I don't appreciate this.

623
00:41:12,017 --> 00:41:12,851
So stop.

624
00:41:14,719 --> 00:41:16,254
He's your student.

625
00:41:17,189 --> 00:41:23,128
Please work on understanding
what is on his mind right now,

626
00:41:23,195 --> 00:41:25,197
or what matters might be troubling him.

627
00:41:26,998 --> 00:41:27,833
Yes, ma'am.

628
00:41:38,610 --> 00:41:40,679
I'm exhausted!

629
00:41:41,246 --> 00:41:44,816
All right, let's got to Miyoshiya.

630
00:41:44,883 --> 00:41:48,954
Not the boxed lunch place,
the place by the beach.

631
00:41:49,020 --> 00:41:51,189
-What about Ms. Shioya?
-She went home.

632
00:41:51,256 --> 00:41:53,892
She had to put
together something for the BOE.

633
00:41:53,959 --> 00:41:56,528
-I'll go park my car somewhere first.
-Okay.

634
00:41:56,595 --> 00:41:58,029
We can head there now.

635
00:42:18,717 --> 00:42:23,288
KUROIWA

636
00:43:16,739 --> 00:43:20,310
Everyone wants to put a label on me.

637
00:43:21,778 --> 00:43:25,148
Women will just get married
and quit right away!

638
00:43:27,750 --> 00:43:28,585
Why tennis?

639
00:43:28,651 --> 00:43:31,087
If they don't,
they're mistresses or old maids.

640
00:43:32,088 --> 00:43:33,590
Or mentally unstable!

641
00:43:36,559 --> 00:43:37,427
Damn it.

642
00:43:38,361 --> 00:43:43,800
Or others close themselves off
when they find out I have a girlfriend.

643
00:43:48,237 --> 00:43:51,040
But you didn't change.

644
00:43:51,874 --> 00:43:52,875
Why not?

645
00:43:53,910 --> 00:43:54,744
Who knows.

646
00:43:56,579 --> 00:43:59,949
Because you're you?

647
00:44:01,884 --> 00:44:02,819
What's that mean?

648
00:44:07,190 --> 00:44:08,791
-Huddle up.
-Okay.

649
00:44:14,764 --> 00:44:18,134
Hijiri called you her goal?

650
00:44:18,701 --> 00:44:20,370
Uh, yes.

651
00:44:20,970 --> 00:44:24,641
You haven't realized a goal is
something that feels distant?

652
00:44:26,142 --> 00:44:30,546
There's a chance she's feeling
distant from you.

653
00:44:34,150 --> 00:44:36,686
<i>Living long distance,</i>
<i>you start drifting apart,</i>

654
00:44:36,753 --> 00:44:38,121
<i>unable to be honest.</i>

655
00:44:39,255 --> 00:44:40,490
Unable to be vulnerable.

656
00:44:41,491 --> 00:44:45,294
You gradually become strangers.

657
00:44:47,997 --> 00:44:49,165
Be careful, Kawai.

658
00:44:50,800 --> 00:44:54,637
So I guess being long-distance
isn't going to work, huh?

659
00:44:55,872 --> 00:44:58,408
If you're worried, start making moves!

660
00:45:02,011 --> 00:45:03,212
Damn it!

661
00:45:03,279 --> 00:45:05,214
I thought I returned that one!

662
00:45:06,983 --> 00:45:07,950
It wasn't bad.

663
00:45:22,665 --> 00:45:23,766
What?

664
00:45:45,021 --> 00:45:47,290
Kuroiwa, you okay?

665
00:45:48,224 --> 00:45:49,092
Did you fall?

666
00:45:50,093 --> 00:45:51,327
Did you hit your head?

667
00:46:02,672 --> 00:46:03,639
Your leg!

668
00:46:06,109 --> 00:46:07,009
Can you stand?

669
00:46:12,415 --> 00:46:13,249
Does it hurt?

670
00:46:25,995 --> 00:46:26,963
Ms. Suenaga.

671
00:46:28,464 --> 00:46:32,101
Please don't come to hate me.

672
00:46:34,570 --> 00:46:35,938
Kuroiwa.

673
00:46:40,176 --> 00:46:43,079
Your bone is digging into me. It hurts.

674
00:46:45,081 --> 00:46:48,951
Come on, we need to patch you up, okay?

675
00:46:49,752 --> 00:46:52,421
And if someone sees us--

676
00:46:55,825 --> 00:47:00,363
I don't care if anyone sees us.

677
00:47:03,466 --> 00:47:05,735
You need to calm down.

678
00:47:20,316 --> 00:47:21,217
I'm going home.

679
00:47:23,786 --> 00:47:24,821
Hold on.

680
00:47:37,733 --> 00:47:39,569
You think your mom's still working?

681
00:47:43,873 --> 00:47:45,608
I'll try calling her again.

682
00:47:57,820 --> 00:47:59,989
So you like that song, Ms. Suenaga?

683
00:48:01,190 --> 00:48:02,024
This?

684
00:48:02,725 --> 00:48:06,362
It's not mine, it's his.

685
00:48:16,906 --> 00:48:20,743
I wasn't joking when I said it.

686
00:48:24,013 --> 00:48:25,348
I love you.

687
00:48:34,523 --> 00:48:40,563
So you can try to twist reality all you
want and try to avoid this situation,

688
00:48:42,798 --> 00:48:46,035
but it's just who I am.

689
00:49:01,784 --> 00:49:04,620
-Is that the last of it, boss?
-Yeah!

690
00:49:09,625 --> 00:49:12,128
She's not answering. What should I do?

691
00:49:13,329 --> 00:49:14,230
Can I take you home?

692
00:49:17,867 --> 00:49:18,834
I don't have a key.

693
00:49:18,901 --> 00:49:20,970
Oh right, you mentioned that.

694
00:49:25,841 --> 00:49:27,576
We need to treat your leg too.

695
00:49:28,878 --> 00:49:29,946
How about the hospital?

696
00:49:30,713 --> 00:49:32,081
No, I'm okay.

697
00:49:42,458 --> 00:49:44,460
He's your student.

698
00:49:48,230 --> 00:49:51,600
Okay, I'll take you to my place
to treat you until I reach your mom.

699
00:50:15,424 --> 00:50:17,827
I forgot the light was out.

700
00:50:17,893 --> 00:50:18,828
Come in.

701
00:50:22,865 --> 00:50:24,567
Wash your wound and wait for me.

702
00:51:13,382 --> 00:51:14,250
Here.

703
00:51:55,024 --> 00:51:55,858
Does it hurt?

704
00:51:57,993 --> 00:51:59,161
I'm okay.

705
00:52:21,784 --> 00:52:23,652
Can I ask you something?

706
00:52:30,359 --> 00:52:33,028
Why are you…

707
00:52:39,101 --> 00:52:40,803
Why are you helping me?

708
00:52:42,071 --> 00:52:43,772
Going this far.

709
00:52:43,839 --> 00:52:47,476
You're hurt, I'm doing what any
teacher would do.

710
00:52:48,344 --> 00:52:49,478
Is that all?

711
00:53:18,340 --> 00:53:19,975
<i>Am I…</i>

712
00:53:22,678 --> 00:53:24,079
<i>being too sensitive?</i>

713
00:53:30,319 --> 00:53:32,021
<i>This isn't good.</i>

714
00:53:39,695 --> 00:53:41,197
Are you okay now?

715
00:53:45,134 --> 00:53:46,101
Kuroiwa.

716
00:53:49,004 --> 00:53:49,905
Listen,

717
00:53:52,441 --> 00:53:53,576
I have someone I love.

718
00:53:57,813 --> 00:53:58,714
So…

719
00:54:13,629 --> 00:54:16,765
Could I borrow some money?

720
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:21,070
I'd like to get something
from the store downstairs.

721
00:54:22,538 --> 00:54:25,374
Right, you must be hungry.
I'll get you a drink.

722
00:54:25,441 --> 00:54:29,044
No, I'll go. I'm worried you might
buy something weird.

723
00:54:29,111 --> 00:54:31,814
-But your leg.
-I'm okay.

724
00:54:32,615 --> 00:54:33,716
Do you need anything?

725
00:54:34,883 --> 00:54:36,218
No, I'm okay.

726
00:55:12,488 --> 00:55:15,124
<i>The person you are</i>
<i>trying to reach is not available.</i>

727
00:55:25,367 --> 00:55:27,803
Kuroiwa, I'll just drive you back--

728
00:55:29,271 --> 00:55:30,239
I bring gifts.

729
00:55:33,909 --> 00:55:36,211
-Thank you.
-Sorry for the surprise.

730
00:55:36,278 --> 00:55:38,747
I had the urge to come see you.

731
00:55:49,358 --> 00:55:50,392
Found something.

732
00:55:52,261 --> 00:55:53,796
It's Akira's crush.

733
00:55:54,596 --> 00:55:55,464
Really?

734
00:56:03,706 --> 00:56:05,374
Isn't this Hijiri his…?

735
00:56:06,075 --> 00:56:07,209
It can't be.

736
00:56:10,646 --> 00:56:11,714
Ms. Suenaga?

737
00:56:29,932 --> 00:56:33,402
Have you done anything to warrant
these torrid rumors?

738
00:56:33,469 --> 00:56:34,570
<i>Kuroiwa's got a girlfriend!</i>

739
00:56:34,636 --> 00:56:36,772
-It's none of your business!
-Of course it's my business!

740
00:56:36,839 --> 00:56:38,974
<i>You can't erase your feelings for someone.</i>

741
00:56:39,041 --> 00:56:39,875
<i>It's impossible.</i>

742
00:56:39,942 --> 00:56:40,909
Subtitle translation by: Zensho Yamamoto

